{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User","sessionId":"ac6da811-9980-485b-b0d8-9339263a742b","version":"2.1.42","gitBranch":"HEAD","agentId":"a289410","slug":"splendid-hugging-penguin","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are building services for the E-E-A-T Builder module in a Vite SPA project at `C:\\Users\\User\\Downloads\\SaaS X-Final-Rick-Test - Test Copie\\`.\n\nThe project uses Google Gemini AI (`@google/genai`) with this exact pattern for all services:\n\n```typescript\nimport { GoogleGenAI, Type, Schema } from \"@google/genai\";\n\nconst getApiKey = () => {\n  if (typeof process !== 'undefined' && process.env && process.env.API_KEY) {\n    return process.env.API_KEY;\n  }\n  return null;\n};\n```\n\nModel: `gemini-2.5-flash`, always with `responseMimeType: 'application/json'`, `responseSchema`, and fallback simulation when no API key.\n\n## FILES TO CREATE\n\n### 1. `services/eeat/prompts.ts`\nExport system prompts for all 6 tools:\n- PROMPT_AUTHOR_BIO — Generate author bios (short 50 words + long 150 words)\n- PROMPT_ABOUT_PAGE — Generate full About page HTML with E-E-A-T signals\n- PROMPT_TRUST_SIGNALS — Generate trust signal blocks HTML\n- PROMPT_CREDENTIALS — Generate expert credentials HTML + Schema.org\n- PROMPT_CITATION_BLOCK — Generate author citation block for articles\n- PROMPT_EEAT_AUDIT — Audit a URL for E-E-A-T score\n\nAll prompts in French, focused on AEO/E-E-A-T optimization.\n\n### 2. `services/eeat/author-bio-generator.ts`\nExport: `generateAuthorBio(profile: AuthorProfile): Promise<GeneratedAuthorBio>`\n- Takes author profile data\n- Returns: bioShort (50 words), bioLong (150 words), Schema.org Person JSON-LD, HTML block\n- Fallback: build realistic bios from the profile data\n\n### 3. `services/eeat/about-page-generator.ts`\nExport: `generateAboutPage(org: OrganizationProfile): Promise<GeneratedAboutPage>`\n- Takes organization profile\n- Returns: full HTML, Schema.org Organization JSON-LD, sections (hero, story, team, values, numbers, certifications, cta)\n- Fallback: generate realistic HTML sections\n\n### 4. `services/eeat/trust-signals-generator.ts`\nExport: `generateTrustSignals(config: TrustSignalsConfig, orgName: string): Promise<GeneratedTrustBlock>`\n- Takes trust signals config\n- Returns: HTML with Tailwind classes, Schema.org for reviews\n- Fallback: generate HTML blocks for certifications, press, reviews, guarantees\n\n### 5. `services/eeat/credentials-generator.ts`\nExport: `generateCredentials(profile: AuthorProfile): Promise<GeneratedCredentials>`\n- Takes author profile with credentials/education/certifications\n- Returns: HTML block, Schema.org with hasCredential/alumniOf/award\n- Fallback: build structured credentials display\n\n### 6. `services/eeat/citation-block-generator.ts`\nExport: `generateCitationBlock(profile: AuthorProfile, articleTitle?: string): Promise<GeneratedCitationBlock>`\n- Takes author profile + optional article context\n- Returns: HTML author box for end of article, Schema.org\n- Fallback: build author box with photo, mini-bio, links, verification date\n\n### 7. `services/eeat/eeat-auditor.ts`\nExport: `auditEeat(url: string, brandName?: string): Promise<EeatAuditResult>`\n- Takes URL + optional brand name\n- Returns: scores (overall, experience, expertise, authority, trust), findings array, priority actions, summary\n- Fallback: deterministic scores based on URL hash, realistic findings in French\n\n### 8. `services/eeat/index.ts`\nBarrel export for all generators.\n\n## IMPORTANT RULES\n- Import types from `../../types/eeat` (the types file exists already)\n- Each service is self-contained with its own getApiKey() helper\n- Each has a robust fallbackSimulation function\n- Gemini calls use structured JSON schema with Type.OBJECT, Type.STRING, Type.NUMBER, Type.ARRAY, Type.BOOLEAN\n- All fallback text is in French\n- Temperature: 0.2-0.3 for factual, 0.4 for creative\n- Clean markdown fences from responses: `output.replace(/\\`\\`\\`json\\n?/g, '').replace(/\\`\\`\\`\\n?/g, '').trim()`\n- Error handling: try/catch, log error, fall back to simulation\n\nWrite all 8 files. Make sure they are complete and production-ready."},"uuid":"c71a41da-9a6e-4861-8bdf-379d9ef2ee86","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:11:58.155Z"}
